## 14. PAGINATION / INFINITE SCROLL

- **Pagination is mandatory** on every data-listing screen. Never fetch the full dataset in one shot.
- Standard pagination state in every list controller:

```dart
final items         = <T>[].obs;
final isLoading     = false.obs;
final isLoadingMore = false.obs;
final hasError      = false.obs;
final hasMore       = true.obs;
int _currentPage    = 1;
static const int _pageSize = 20;
```

- `ScrollController` lives in the **controller**, disposed in `onClose()`.
- Trigger `fetchMore()` when 200 px from bottom:

```dart
void _onScroll() {
  final pos = scrollController.position;
  if (pos.pixels >= pos.maxScrollExtent - 200) fetchMore();
}
```

- Keep initial load (`isLoading`) and append load (`isLoadingMore`) as separate states.
- End of list: localized "all loaded" message when `hasMore == false`; small spinner when `isLoadingMore == true`.
- `RefreshIndicator` for pull-to-refresh: reset `_currentPage`, clear list, refetch.

